The backend of VitalAI is designed to handle secure data processing, Machine Learning integration, authentication, and real-time prediction services efficiently. It acts as the core communication layer between the frontend interface, the AI prediction model, and the database system.
Built using modern backend frameworks and RESTful APIs, the server manages user requests, validates medical input data, processes prediction queries, and returns AI-generated cardiovascular risk analysis results in real time. The backend also handles authentication systems, session management, protected routes, and secure API communication to ensure data privacy and reliability.
The system integrates Machine Learning models for heart disease prediction, enabling seamless inference and fast response times. It also supports database connectivity for storing user profiles, prediction history, medical records, and application settings. Additional features such as error handling, API optimization, scalability support, logging, and modular architecture make the backend robust, maintainable, and production-ready for healthcare analytics applications.
